"title": "7555: Sadducees",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7555",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>An influential Jewish party that denied the existence of the spirit world and the possibility of resurrection. Its members are portrayed as opposing Jesus Christ and the first Christians.</p>\n<h2>Many priests were Sadducees</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:17\">ACT 5:17</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Sadducees rejected the concepts of resurrection and spirit world</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts23:8\">ACT 23:8</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Sadducees questioned Jesus Christ about the resurrection</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:23-Matt22:32\">MAT 22:23–22:32</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:18-Mark12:27\">MRK 12:18–12:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:27-Luke20:38\">LUK 20:27–20:38</a></p>\n<h2>Sadducees denounced by John the Baptist</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt3:7-Matt3:10\">MAT 3:7–3:10</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Sadducees denounced by Jesus Christ</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:6-Matt16:12\">MAT 16:6–16:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:28-Matt21:45\">MAT 21:28–21:45</a> <em>The chief priests were probably Sadducees (see <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:17\">Ac 5:17</a>).</em></p>\n<h2>The Sadducees oppose the first Christians</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:1-Acts4:3\">ACT 4:1–4:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:17-Acts5:18\">ACT 5:17–5:18</a></p>",
